  "prompt": "Is Sania Mirza has gone rogue in Olympic bronze match. Where is her world class form, in doubles?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, there is no record of Sania Mirza participating in an Olympic bronze medal match or behaving in a manner that could be described as \"going rogue\" during such an event. Sania Mirza, a celebrated Indian tennis player, has had a distinguished career primarily in women's doubles, achieving significant success in Grand Slam tournaments and elevating the profile of Indian tennis on the global stage.\n\n### Olympic Participation\nSania Mirza has not competed in the Olympic Games. Despite her impressive doubles career, she did not represent India in the Olympics. There could be various reasons for this, including scheduling conflicts, competition selection processes, or her personal decisions regarding participation.\n\n### Retirement and Current Status\nAs of 2023, Sania Mirza has announced her retirement from professional tennis. This decision marked the end of an era for Indian tennis, as she was one of the most prominent and influential players from the country. Her retirement means she is no longer actively competing in tournaments, including doubles events.\n\n### Legacy in Doubles\nThroughout her career, Sania Mirza was known for her exceptional skills in doubles. She has won multiple Grand Slam titles and has been a key figure in popularizing tennis in India. Her partnerships with various players, including Martina Hingis, were highly successful and showcased her ability to excel at the highest levels of the sport.\n\n### Conclusion\nIf there have been any recent developments beyond October 2023 concerning Sania Mirza's participation in Olympic events or other aspects of her career, I would recommend checking the latest reliable sources or official announcements for the most up-to-date information.",
